<h1 id="hd_id3150278" xml-lang="en-US"><link href="text/shared/01/05260100.xhp" name="To Page">To Page</link></h1>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3150756" xml-lang="en-US"><ahelp hid=".uno:SetAnchorToPage">Anchors the selected object so that it always remains on the current page.</ahelp></paragraph>
</section>
<section id="howtoget">
<embed href="text/shared/00/00040501.xhp#to-page"/>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id781653782304845">Objects with this anchor can be positioned in relation to the entire page or in relation to the pageâ€™s text area.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3149987" xml-lang="en-US">The position of the anchored object on the current page does not change as content and pages are added or removed from the document.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id11653782256765"> The current page remains in the document, with its current position in the sequence of pages, as long as the object is anchored to that page.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3152821" xml-lang="en-US">The anchor icon is displayed at the top left corner of the page.</paragraph>
